    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Oil Cooler and Filter Housing - Cleaning,
        Inspection, and Testing - Oil Cooler Pressure Test
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="test" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Oil Cooler Pressure Test</title>
        <figure id="e3001017" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ13/J13038.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil cooler air pressure leakage test</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air pressure regulator</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air adapter (make locally)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Test plate</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If oil cooler is leaking, replace the oil cooler assembly. There are no serviceable parts for this
                    unit.
                </para>
            </note>
            <note>
                <para>The oil filter base must be installed on the oil cooler cover assembly before pressure testing.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para id="S3001001" count="1">Fabricate an air adapter with the following items:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Rubber hose</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Reducer bushing (hose to fitting)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Shop air fitting (male)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Two clamps</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fasten
                <hotlnk document="eges390_223.xml" xrefid="E30010C" appearance="hottext">Oil Cooler Pressure Test
                    Plate
                </hotlnk>
                <xref refid="E30010C"/>
                to oil cooler assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install air pressure regulator to EGR cooler coolant outlet port (air adapter).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply 207 kPa (30 psi) of air pressure.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Spray a soapy water solution around oil cooler and oil filter base.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not submerge the oil cooler in water. Submerging can allow water into
                    oil passages.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If leaking, bubbles will be present. Replace leaking component or seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove soapy water residue and blow off with filtered compressed air.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
